@ScottHalpernMD Thank you! What do you think the true mortality rate for patients getting out of the ICU in the US will be for Covid patients? How much different than typical ARDS? The numbers are grim (but very small sample sizes) from studies from other countries.

One doc told me he was on a call with a former ICU patient who said, "Oh my gosh, we are really experts in surviving the ICU. We have been out the other side. We know how to do this, and we are going to be a unique resource -- ICU survivors in the era of covid."

Reporting this story was very unsettling. The notion that overcoming ventilator shortages, limited ICU beds, the coronavirus itself, someone's life could be saved!!!
And yet --that's the beginning of a really difficult second journey https://t.co/LTQuRo6RCw

People with critical cases of covid-19 are isolated from their families in the ICU and are often depend on mechanical ventilators for 1-2 weeks. The long-term effects could be the next health crisis. https://t.co/gwEKEvu4IP
